<main id="main">
    <h1>Managing boards</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>When using boards you can visualise the workflow of a project or a working process within your company. Common boards consist of three columns: <em>To do</em>, <em>Doing</em> and <em>Done</em>. You decide about the structure of the board and how many columns you add.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="10">1. Creating a board</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to create a board.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a board:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Boards</strong>.<br>
→ <strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>→ The <strong>Boards</strong> tab opens in a new tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Create new board</strong>.<br>
→ The window <strong>Create new board</strong> opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the name of the board.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The board is created and added to the list.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="20">2. Adding a column</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to add columns to the board. You can add as many columns as you like.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Adding a column:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Boards</strong>.<br>
→ <strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>→ The <strong>Boards</strong> tab opens in a new tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the board that you want to edit.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add new column</strong>.<br>
→ The column is added to the left side.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the name of the column.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Add further columns in the same way until you have the desired number of columns for the board.<br>
→ <strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> You can change the position of the columns.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="30">3. Adding a card</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to add cards to the board. You can add as many cards as you like.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Adding a card:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Boards</strong>.<br>
→ <strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>→ The <strong>Boards</strong> tab opens in a new tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the board that you want to edit.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add new card</strong> in the column that you want to add a card to.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the name of the card.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Save new card</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Add further cards in the same way until you have the desired number of cards for the board.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="40">4. Editing a card</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can edit the cards on the board at any time. Link the cards to a contact, an order and a ticket, for example, or add an owner and tags. To do so, proceed as described below.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Adding a card:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Boards</strong>.<br>
→ <strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>→ The <strong>Boards</strong> tab opens in a new tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the board that you want to edit.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the card’s arrow in the right to edit the card.<br>
→ The settings menu opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-boards-edit-card">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
